post_text:
Important Notice Regarding the Sodus CSD Budget Vote and BOE Election
Per Executive Order 202.39, the date for the District to receive absentee ballots has been moved to 5:00 p.m. on June 16, 2020. Details are as follows:



Sodus CSD is able to receive absentee ballots via personal delivery through 5:00 p.m. on June 9, 2020, only. A drop box is located outside the Sodus CSD District Office located at 6375 Robinson Road. After this deadline, the District may no longer accept absentee ballots in person.
Sodus CSD will continue to receive absentee ballots via the USPS through 5:00 p.m. on June 16, 2020.
On June 16, 2020, after 5:00 p.m., Sodus CSD will begin the process of counting absentee ballots.

If you have any questions, please contact Regina Moline, District Clerk, at rmoline@soduscsd.org or (315) 483-5201.

post_text:
We received approval to expand the lunch and breakfast program we are offering at the Elementary School. As you are aware, we are using a grab and go system. If you are unable to come and pick up meals, feel free to send a neighbor, friend, family member, whomever is able to help you out. We have had many families work together for this purpose and we love seeing that. I am happy to report that we received approval to continue this during the scheduled April break. Yes, we will continue to deliver breakfast and lunch Monday through Friday’s up until we return on April 14th. Even better, we received approval to provide every child with meals for the weekend when they pick up on Friday (every child will receive 3 lunches and 3 breakfasts on Friday). The weekend meal program will start this Friday, March 27th. Once again, this program runs Monday through Friday from 10:30 – 12:30 at
the Elementary School. Just follow the signs to the back of the building.
